               <head>Grant; Needham Street, etc.; 1315</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Needham-Street etc)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1315">1315</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> le <surname>Fole</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteford)</placeName>, miller</persName>, to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Priour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham, in the parish of Gayslee)</placeName></persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>Petronilla</forename> his wife</persName>, for certain sum of money, of two acres of arable land, in four parcels, lying at the upper end of the parish of <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName>, in the field called <placeName type="minor">Caremenecroftes</placeName>, next to the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Beyllard</surname></persName>, one end abutting on the common heath, the other on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> 
                           <surname>Mariscal</surname></persName>.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, Monday [1 Dec.] before the feast of St Nicholas, bishop and confessor, 9 Edw. II [1315].
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperlyng</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> 
                           <surname>Mariscal</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Warner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> 
                           <surname>(Townsend) 'ad caput ville'</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Dersoun</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) 'Fabro'</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName></persName>, and others.
                     The seal is wanting.
                     </p>
